                            <comment id="15296646" author="cutting" created="Mon, 23 May 2016 16:57:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just added you as an owner in PiPI and RubyGems.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15296660" author="rdblue" created="Mon, 23 May 2016 17:08:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks! I&apos;ll get those updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15297476" author="mtth" created="Tue, 24 May 2016 01:15:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rdblue&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rdblue&quot;&gt;Ryan Blue&lt;/a&gt; - just added you as collaborator to avro-js. Let me know if you run into any issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15298338" author="rdblue" created="Tue, 24 May 2016 15:14:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I ran into issues with the js publication, but not related to npm. Looks like the version in our package.json was hard-coded to 1.8.0, so the signed release tarball has version 1.8.0 instead of 1.8.1 and can&apos;t be uploaded to npm. I think we should just go ahead and do another release for just the js component. Any interest in being RM for it? Otherwise I&apos;ll call a vote soon-ish.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
